folder: Chrystie Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
No. 141 Chrystie Street, adjoining the S.W. corner of Delancey Street. This view shows the Camp Memorial Church organized in 1859, when the Bowery was known as the "Promenade".

About 1920.

Brown Brothers.

folder: Delancey Street & Chrystie Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Delancey Street, north side, at and including Chrystie Street. View shows partial completion of Libby's Hotel.

About 1924.

Underwood & Underwood.

folder: Chrystie Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Chrystie Street, north from but not including Delancey Street.

July 18, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

folder: Delancey Street & Chrystie Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1) Delancey Street, north side, east from and including Chrystie Street, to and including Forsyth Street. The view shows Libby's Hotel. NEG# 2962 September 21, 1929. P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing a closer view of Libby's Hotel. September 21, 1929. P. L. Sperr.

(3) The same, from a different angle. July 23, 1930. P. L. Sperr.  Negative # 3933

folder: Chrystie Street & Delancey Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Chrystie Street, west side, north to but not including Delancey Street, from Broome Street. The view shows Broome Street, north side, from but not including Forsyth Street, to the Bowery. In the foreground is the excavation for the Roosevelt Park site.

July 23, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

text:
Chrystie Street, east side, north from but not including Delancey Street, to but not including Rivington Street. The buildings are being wrecked to clear site for Roosevelt Park.

May 9, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.
